title: SFH on dengue fever (with photos)
content_text:
p>
	Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food and 
	Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after inspecting mosquito prevention and control 
	measures in Sha Tin today (April 14): Reporter: (On dengue fever.) Secretary for Food and Health: In the past three years from 2011 to 2013, 
	there was no report of local dengue fever cases. However, there were a total 
	of three local dengue fever cases, together with over a hundred imported

of three local dengue fever cases, together with over a hundred imported 
	cases, last year. The situation in neighbouring areas, e.g. Singapore, 
	Guangdong, Taiwan, is a matter of particular concern. The outbreaks of 
	dengue fever in these places last year were severe. That's why there are 
	reasons to believe that if we do not mount a very forceful anti-mosquito 
	campaign this year, a serious outbreak of dengue fever in Hong Kong can be

campaign this year, a serious outbreak of dengue fever in Hong Kong can be 
	predicted. Reporter: (On anti-mosquito efforts.) Secretary for Food and Health: There are two particular aspects that we 
	would advise the general public to pay attention to. Firstly, they should 
	pay attention to wherever places that water can accumulate and clear 
	stagnant water. Secondly, take anti-mosquito measures during outdoor 
	activities. (Please also refer to the

activities. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.) Ends/Tuesday, April 14, 2015
Issued at HKT 18:57
